The way some people have berated them is absolutely atrocious. This is literally their life's work, and not only are they themselves involved, but they have other contributors too. It has taken them a full 4 years to accomplish this goal, and at the bare minimum it is completely their right to put some monetary value on this end product.
Now, even I cannot pay to watch the documentary, but it's more than worth it to wait a couple of weeks rather than creating a ruckus about it. A few weeks is not hurting you, and if you do want to watch it that badly, then just pay the one dollar. Kara and Nate did mess up in not releasing the vlog and instead putting it with the documentary, and that did upset some people (including myself) and understandably so. However, a full length documentary is vastly different from a 15 minute long vlog, and just the fact that they are actually publishing it FOR FREE in February is a very mindblowing feat.
It's saddening to see that this has resulted in hours of stress for both Kara and Nate, as well as forced them to make the documentary completely free AND release it earlier than planned.
